<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="114" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/6557</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Diplomatic and
                                        Consular Officers in All Countries</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-29T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Note and advise consular officers your jurisdiction that War Trade
                                Board has granted general license authorizing trans-shipment in
                                United States ports of all goods destined for Mexican, Central
                                American and South American ports, which have been allowed to go
                                forward by British, French or Italian authorities, even though
                                consignees are on enemy trading list.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>